156
00:13:15.040 --> 00:13:16.087
Yes.

157
00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:18.481
Ava.

158
00:13:20.120 --> 00:13:22.009
I'm pleased
to meet you. Ava.

159
00:13:22.720 --> 00:13:24.927
I'm pleased
to meet you. too.

160
00:13:26.720 --> 00:13:29.121
I've never met
anyone new before.

161
00:13:29.840 --> 00:13:31.251
Only Nathan.

162
00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:35.848
Then I guess we're both
in quite a similar position.

163
00:13:35.960 --> 00:13:38.406
Haven't you met
lots of new people before?

164
00:13:39.400 --> 00:13:40.925
None like you.

165
00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:42.201
Hmm.

166
00:13:45.200 --> 00:13:47.328
So we need
to break the ice.

167
00:13:48.240 --> 00:13:50.368
Do you know what
I mean by that?
Yes.

168
00:13:50.440 --> 00:13:51.726
What do I mean?

169
00:13:51.800 --> 00:13:54.326
Overcome initial
social awkwardness.

170
00:13:54.920 --> 00:13:56.365
So let's have
a conversation.

171
00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:58.521
AVA: Okay.

172
00:14:00.760 --> 00:14:02.967
<i>What would you like to have
a conversation about?</i>

173
00:14:03.040 --> 00:14:05.611
Why don't we start with you telling
me something about yourself?

174
00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:08.287
What would you
like to know?

175
00:14:08.480 --> 00:14:10.209
Whatever comes
into your head.

176
00:14:10.280 --> 00:14:13.568
Well. you already
know my name.

177
00:14:14.760 --> 00:14:17.081
And you can see
that I'm a machine.

178
00:14:17.480 --> 00:14:19.767
Would you like to know
how old I am?
Sure.

179
00:14:20.120 --> 00:14:21.121
I'm one.

180
00:14:21.440 --> 00:14:22.726
One what?

181
00:14:23.600 --> 00:14:25.602
One year or one day?
One.

182
00:14:29.440 --> 00:14:31.761
When did you learn
how to speak. Ava?

183
00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:35.128
<i>I always knew
how to speak.</i>

184
00:14:35.720 --> 00:14:38.007
<i>and that's strange.
isn't it?</i>

185
00:14:38.520 --> 00:14:39.601
Why?

186
00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:43.209
Because language is something
that people acquire.

187
00:14:43.960 --> 00:14:46.122
Well.
some people believe

188
00:14:46.200 --> 00:14:47.804
language exists from birth.

189
00:14:48.160 --> 00:14:50.561
And what is learned is the
ability to attach words

190
00:14:50.640 --> 00:14:53.041
and structure to the latent ability.
Do you agree with that?

191
00:14:53.520 --> 00:14:54.965
<i>I don't know.</i>

192
00:14:56.680 --> 00:14:59.206
<i>Will you come back
tomorrow. Caleb?</i>

193
00:15:00.240 --> 00:15:01.321
<i>Yes.</i>

194
00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:04.481
(CHUCKLES)

195
00:15:05.680 --> 00:15:06.966
<i>Good.</i>

196
00:15:14.840 --> 00:15:16.968
Oh. man.
she's fascinating.

197
00:15:18.080 --> 00:15:20.651
When you talk to her.
you're just...

198
00:15:20.840 --> 00:15:22.330
Through the looking glass.

199
00:15:22.920 --> 00:15:25.366
"Through the looking glass."
Wow.

200
00:15:25.680 --> 00:15:27.569
You're good with words. Caleb.
You're quotable.

201
00:15:27.680 --> 00:15:28.886
Actually. that's
someone else's quote.

202
00:15:28.960 --> 00:15:31.850
You know. I wrote down that
other line you came up with.

203
00:15:31.920 --> 00:15:33.046
The one about how

204
00:15:33.160 --> 00:15:34.960
if I've invented a machine
with consciousness.

205
00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:36.525
I'm not a man. I'm God.

206
00:15:36.600 --> 00:15:37.840
I don't think
that's exactly what I...

207
00:15:37.920 --> 00:15:40.127
I just thought.
"Fuck. man. that is so good."

208
00:15:40.200 --> 00:15:42.601
When we get to
tell the story. You know?

209
00:15:42.680 --> 00:15:44.409
I turned to Caleb.

210
00:15:44.680 --> 00:15:47.126
and he looked up at me
and he said.

211
00:15:47.200 --> 00:15:48.440
"You're not a man.
you're God."

212
00:15:48.520 --> 00:15:50.040
(STUTTERS) Yeah.
but I didn't say that.

213
00:15:50.640 --> 00:15:51.766
So...

214
00:15:51.840 --> 00:15:53.046
anyway.

215
00:15:55.960 --> 00:15:56.961
You're impressed.

216
00:15:57.160 --> 00:15:59.208
(LAUGHING) Yes. Yes.

217
00:16:00.040 --> 00:16:02.281
Although...
Although? (LAUGHING)

218
00:16:02.840 --> 00:16:04.680
There's a qualification
to you being impressed?

219
00:16:04.720 --> 00:16:07.200
No. there's no
qualification to her.

220
00:16:07.720 --> 00:16:09.927
Uh. it's just
in the Turing Test.

221
00:16:10.200 --> 00:16:12.123
the machine should be
hidden from the examiner.

222
00:16:12.240 --> 00:16:13.810
No. no. no.
we're way past that.

223
00:16:13.880 --> 00:16:15.291
If I hid Ava from you.

224
00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:17.647
so you just heard her voice.
she would pass for human.

225
00:16:17.720 --> 00:16:20.610
The real test is to show you
that she's a robot

226
00:16:20.680 --> 00:16:23.490
and then see if you still
feel she has consciousness.

227
00:16:23.560 --> 00:16:24.607
Mmm.

228
00:16:25.560 --> 00:16:27.085
Yeah. I think
you're probably right.

229
00:16:27.280 --> 00:16:28.441
(CHUCKLES)

230
00:16:28.800 --> 00:16:32.486
Her language abilities.
they're incredible.

231
00:16:32.560 --> 00:16:36.531
The system is stochastic.
Right?

232
00:16:37.520 --> 00:16:39.409
It's non-deterministic.

233
00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:40.686
At first I thought
she was mapping

234
00:16:40.760 --> 00:16:43.525
from internal semantic form
to syntactic tree-structure

235
00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:44.840
and then getting
linearized words.

236
00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:47.685
But then I started to realize the
model was some kind of hybrid.

237
00:16:47.760 --> 00:16:48.966
Caleb.

238
00:16:49.640 --> 00:16:50.641
No?

239
00:16:50.720 --> 00:16:54.088
I understand that you want
me to explain how Ava works.

240
00:16:54.200 --> 00:16:56.362
But I'm sorry.
I'm not gonna be
able to do that.

241
00:16:56.440 --> 00:16:59.171
Try me. I'm hot
on high-level abstraction.

242
00:16:59.240 --> 00:17:02.050
It's not because I think
you're too dumb.

243
00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:04.242
It's because I want to have a
beer and a conversation with you.

244
00:17:04.320 --> 00:17:05.367
Not a seminar.

245
00:17:05.440 --> 00:17:07.807
(CHUCKLES)
Yeah. Sorry.

246
00:17:08.280 --> 00:17:10.601
No. it's okay.
You're all right.

247
00:17:10.680 --> 00:17:11.966
Just...

248
00:17:14.120 --> 00:17:15.610
Answer me this.

249
00:17:16.360 --> 00:17:18.408
How do you feel
about her?

250
00:17:19.440 --> 00:17:21.204
Nothing analytical.

251
00:17:21.600 --> 00:17:23.807
Just how do you feel?

252
00:17:24.640 --> 00:17:25.801
I feel

253
00:17:28.520 --> 00:17:30.648
that she's fucking amazing.

254
00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:33.126
Dude.

255
00:17:34.120 --> 00:17:35.121
Cheers.

256
00:17:36.880 --> 00:17:38.166
Cheers.

257
00:17:40.320 --> 00:17:41.970
(MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO)

258
00:18:09.120 --> 00:18:10.281
(EXHALES)

259
00:18:15.880 --> 00:18:17.120
Damn it.

