329
00:25:15.360 --> 00:25:18.204
And it won't tell you
if it knows what chess is.

330
00:25:18.520 --> 00:25:20.522
Uh-huh. So it's
simulation versus actual.

331
00:25:20.600 --> 00:25:21.965
Yes. Yeah.

332
00:25:22.440 --> 00:25:25.250
And I think being able to
differentiate between those two

333
00:25:25.320 --> 00:25:27.209
is the Turing Test
you want me to perform.

334
00:25:27.280 --> 00:25:29.886
Look. do me a favor.
Lay off the textbook approach.

335
00:25:29.960 --> 00:25:32.566
I just want simple answers
to simple questions.

336
00:25:33.000 --> 00:25:34.729
Yesterday I asked you
how you felt about her

337
00:25:34.800 --> 00:25:36.404
and you gave me
a great answer.

338
00:25:37.160 --> 00:25:38.969
Now the question is.

339
00:25:40.160 --> 00:25:42.288
how does she feel
about you?

340
00:25:48.920 --> 00:25:50.604
What do you think?

341
00:25:54.240 --> 00:25:56.242
CALEB: What is it
a drawing of?

342
00:25:57.200 --> 00:25:58.725
Don't you know?

343
00:25:58.920 --> 00:26:01.400
No.
I thought you would tell me.

344
00:26:02.760 --> 00:26:04.330
Don't you know?

345
00:26:06.680 --> 00:26:08.682
I do drawings every day.

346
00:26:09.400 --> 00:26:11.846
But I never know
what they're of.

347
00:26:12.600 --> 00:26:15.683
Are you not trying to
sketch something specific?

348
00:26:16.320 --> 00:26:18.607
Like an object or a person?

349
00:26:22.480 --> 00:26:24.244
Maybe you could try.

350
00:26:26.520 --> 00:26:27.646
Okay.

351
00:26:29.680 --> 00:26:31.728
What object should I draw?

352
00:26:32.520 --> 00:26:35.046
Whatever you want.
It's your decision.

353
00:26:35.120 --> 00:26:36.884
Why is it my decision?

354
00:26:36.960 --> 00:26:39.770
I'm interested to see
what you'll choose.

355
00:27:01.520 --> 00:27:03.204
Do you want
to be my friend?

356
00:27:04.880 --> 00:27:05.881
Of course.

357
00:27:06.000 --> 00:27:07.809
Will it be possible?

358
00:27:08.160 --> 00:27:09.321
Why would it not be?

359
